A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring Mary Kay Murphy for a lifetime of distinguished service to education and
2 community; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Mary Kay Murphy has dedicated her life to the pursuit of excellence in
4 education, earning a PhD in education administration from Georgia State University, a
5 master's degree in education and English from Emory University, and a Bachelor of Arts in
6 English and philosophy from Loretto Heights College; and
7 WHEREAS, Mary Kay Murphy has exemplified an outstanding commitment to the teaching
8 profession, with seven years of experience as a public-school teacher in Georgia and
9 California, inspiring students in grades 9 through 12; and
10 WHEREAS, she has played a pivotal role in the advancement of educational institutions
11 through her extraordinary career in private fundraising, securing over $475 million in support
12 of academic programs, faculty research, and campus infrastructure, thereby enhancing
13 educational opportunities for countless students; and
14 WHEREAS, Mary Kay Murphy has shown exemplary dedication to her community, serving
15 as a volunteer teacher at Hopewell Baptist Church, a longtime member of Mary Our Queen
