16 Catholic Church, and as President of the Kiwanis Club of Atlanta, becoming the first woman
17 to hold that office in 80 years; and
18 WHEREAS, her leadership has significantly impacted public education as an elected member
19 of the Gwinnett County School Board for over two decades, during which time she was
20 elected chairman five times and vice chairman five times, ensuring the continued growth and
21 success of the district; and
22 WHEREAS, Mary Kay Murphy has extended her service beyond education, contributing as
23 a civilian representative to the National Security Seminar at the United States Army War
24 College and as a member of numerous civic organizations, including Leadership Atlanta and
25 the Development Committee of the Catholic Archdiocese of Atlanta; and
26 WHEREAS, her exceptional contributions have been recognized through numerous
27 prestigious awards, including the Scott Hudgens Distinguished Citizen Award, Paul Duke
28 Lifetime Achievement Award, and the Gwinnett Chamber of Commerce Award for Service
29 in Public Education; and
30 WHEREAS, Mary Kay Murphy alongside her husband, Michael C. Murphy, a distinguished
31 retired attorney and civic leader, has raised three daughters and is a proud grandparent of
32 two, further demonstrating her dedication to family and community; and
33 WHEREAS, Mary Kay Murphy's lifetime of unwavering commitment to education, civic
34 leadership, and community service will leave a lasting legacy, and she stands as a beacon of
35 inspiration for future generations.
